{# Chunk-pipeline backlog fragment — lazy-loaded via htmx from
   ``GET /status/backlog``. The counts here are full-table aggregate
   scans over ``chunks`` (three per-pass claim-mirroring queries), so
   they're the slowest part of the Status page; deferring them keeps the
   initial page render snappy and streams this panel in when ready.

   ``pending = 0`` means the worker is caught up; a growing number means
   the embedder / keyword extractor / summarizer can't keep up with
   ingest. -1 = query failed (schema drift). #}
{# Counts are scoped to each pass's *eligible* universe (the chunks its
   claim query would actually process — skipped kinds / no_index / short
   / un-embedded chunks are excluded), so ``pending`` is the real
   claimable backlog. The stacked bar splits the universe three ways:
   done (green) + pending (blue) + failed (red). ``failed`` = terminal
   ``status='failed'`` rows the worker never retries (embed/summarize
   only); a non-zero red tail flags chunks stuck out of the corpus. #}
<div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2 text-[11px] text-slate-500">
  <span class="flex items-center gap-1"><span class="inline-block w-3 h-2 rounded-sm bg-emerald-500"></span>done</span>
  <span class="flex items-center gap-1"><span class="inline-block w-3 h-2 rounded-sm bg-sky-500"></span>pending</span>
  <span class="flex items-center gap-1"><span class="inline-block w-3 h-2 rounded-sm bg-amber-400"></span>blocked (waiting on embed)</span>
  <span class="flex items-center gap-1"><span class="inline-block w-3 h-2 rounded-sm bg-rose-500"></span>failed (terminal, never retried)</span>
</div>
<div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white divide-y divide-slate-100">
  {% for pass_name, row in backlog.items() %}
  {% set failed = row.failed|default(0) %}
  {% set blocked = row.blocked|default(0) %}
  {% set total = row.pending + row.done + failed + blocked %}
  {# ``pct`` is percent *complete* (done / total). ``pct_pend`` /
     ``pct_block`` / ``pct_fail`` size the other segments so they stack
     to 100%. ``blocked`` = eligible chunks waiting on an upstream artifact
     (keywords need the embedding first) — real backlog, not done. #}
  {% set pct = ((row.done / total) * 100) if total > 0 else 100 %}
  {% set pct_pend = ((row.pending / total) * 100) if total > 0 else 0 %}
  {% set pct_block = ((blocked / total) * 100) if total > 0 else 0 %}
  {% set pct_fail = ((failed / total) * 100) if total > 0 else 0 %}
  <div class="px-4 py-2 text-xs flex items-center gap-2">
    <span class="font-mono text-slate-700 w-36 shrink-0">{{ pass_name }}</span>
    {% if row.pending == -1 %}
    <span class="text-rose-600">(query failed — see logs)</span>
    {% else %}
    <span class="w-44 shrink-0 tabular-nums" title="{{ '{:,}'.format(total) }} eligible chunks">
      <span class="font-medium {% if row.pending > 0 %}text-amber-700{% else %}text-emerald-700{% endif %}">{{ '{:,}'.format(row.pending) }}</span><span class="text-slate-400"> pending</span>{% if blocked > 0 %}<span class="text-amber-600"> · {{ '{:,}'.format(blocked) }} blocked</span>{% endif %}{% if failed > 0 %}<span class="text-rose-600"> · {{ '{:,}'.format(failed) }} failed</span>{% endif %}
    </span>
    <div class="flex-1 h-2 rounded bg-slate-100 overflow-hidden flex"
         title="done {{ '{:,}'.format(row.done) }} · pending {{ '{:,}'.format(row.pending) }} · blocked {{ '{:,}'.format(blocked) }} · failed {{ '{:,}'.format(failed) }}">
      <div class="h-2 bg-emerald-500" style="width: {{ '%.1f'|format(pct) }}%"></div>
      <div class="h-2 bg-sky-500" style="width: {{ '%.1f'|format(pct_pend) }}%"></div>
      <div class="h-2 bg-amber-400" style="width: {{ '%.1f'|format(pct_block) }}%"></div>
      <div class="h-2 bg-rose-500" style="width: {{ '%.1f'|format(pct_fail) }}%"></div>
    </div>
    <span class="w-20 text-right text-slate-500 tabular-nums">{{ '%.1f'|format(pct) }}% done</span>
    <span class="w-24 text-right text-slate-400 shrink-0 tabular-nums"
          title="last productive batch{% if row.last_ts %} — {{ row.last_ts | abs_ts }}{% endif %}">
      {% if row.last_ts %}{{ row.last_ts | ago }}{% else %}—{% endif %}
    </span>
    {% endif %}
  </div>
  {% else %}
  <div class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-slate-500">no backlog data</div>
  {% endfor %}
</div>
